    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1888-03-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1888-03-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="185" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d185">
                <head>No. 185.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Denby</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Bayard</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1888-03-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">March</hi> 19, 1888</date>.
                            (Received May 5.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 593.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to report that the Tsung-li
                        Yamên has agreed to instruct the governor of Formosa to cease the imposition
                        of lekin on native produce, the property of foreigners, within any open port
                        or while in transit from such port to the place of shipment.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Charles
                            Denby.</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
